        <num>CC 1586</num>
        <heading>1586.  General legacy</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1586.  General legacy
A general legacy is a disposition by which the testator bequeaths a fraction or a certain proportion of the estate, or a fraction or certain proportion of the balance of the estate that remains after particular legacies.  In addition, a disposition of property expressly described by the testator as all, or a fraction or a certain proportion of one of the following categories of property, is also a general legacy:  separate or community property, movable or immovable property, or corporeal or incorporeal property.  This list of categories is exclusive.</p>
        </content>
